id=dresosmicrog
name=DresOS microG
version=v3.1.0
versionCode=30100
author=DresOperatingSystems
description=Universal systemless microG suite. Ships the officially signed microG GmsCore 0.3.15, Companion and GsfProxy as privileged system apps under product, with a privapp-permissions allowlist regenerated from the bundled manifests at build time so a microG update can never reintroduce a permission-mismatch bootloop, plus Aurora Store and Aurora Services when available. DroidGuard is built into GmsCore now, so no separate DroidGuard app is shipped. If real Google Play Services is present it is masked systemlessly (reversible) so microG can take over the package names, which fixes installs on stock firmware that previously aborted. A minimal bootloop watchdog auto-disables only this module if a boot never completes, so a bad ROM recovers on its own. No Zygisk payload, no Xposed, and it never touches other modules, so it coexists with the DresOS WebView module. Signature spoofing is provided by the ROM: the microG APKs carry the official microG key, so any ROM with microG signature spoofing (LineageOS 2024-02-26+, e OS, CalyxOS, iodeOS, DivestOS and similar) spoofs them automatically. On a ROM without spoofing microG still installs but signature-checking apps will not work, and the installer says so plainly. An optional stock flavor signs the bundled microG with Google's own certificate via apksigcopier, so it needs no signature spoofing and works on stock firmware and any ROM (system-app only; microG cannot then be updated from F-Droid). Refuses to install on GrapheneOS. Android 8 through 16, all ABIs.
support=https://github.com/DresOperatingSystems/DresOS-Magisk-Modules/issues
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DresOperatingSystems/DresOS-Magisk-Modules/main/microg/update.json
minMagisk=24000
